{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"boreal-unhumane-hoopoe","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Why\n\n`src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_differ.py` is 805 LOC — 5 over the 800 soft cap — and is grandfathered on the module-size allowlist (ceiling 806). Graduate it off the allowlist by splitting on the call-graph seam docs/architecture.md already records: the hand-maintained Jira->local field/status translation layer.\n\n## What\n\nExtract the self-contained Jira->local *translation* cluster into a new leaf module `inbound_fields.py` (same package). Moved symbols (a cohesive, one-way-dependency cluster — the new module references nothing that stays behind):\n- `_load_adf` (+ `_ADF_KEY_INBOUND`, `_AdfModule_Inbound`)\n- translation maps `_JIRA_TO_LOCAL_TYPE`, `_JIRA_TO_LOCAL_PRIORITY`, `_JIRA_TO_LOCAL_STATUS`, `_REBAR_STATUS_LABEL_TO_LOCAL`\n- `_extract_jira_field_value`, `_assignee_matches`, `_normalize_jira_body`, `_map_jira_to_local_fields`\n\n`inbound_differ.py` imports these back from `inbound_fields` and RE-EXPORTS them (so `inbound_differ.<symbol>` attribute access and the config/parity tests keep resolving). The scalar-field diff (`_diff_jira_vs_local`), sub-entity diffs (`_diff_comments_inbound`/`_diff_links_inbound`/`_diff_labels_inbound`), `_EXCLUDED_PREFIXES`, `_load_link_direction`, `_OUTBOUND_TO_INBOUND_FIELD`, `_build_outbound_context`, and `compute_inbound_mutations` all STAY. Pure refactor — no behavior change, no signature change.\n\nThen graduate the file off the gate: remove its row from `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt` AND `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt`, and delete its remedy row in `docs/architecture.md`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `inbound_fields.py` exists, is between 100 and 800 LOC, and contains the moved translation cluster (verify: `wc -l src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_fields.py`)\n- [ ] `inbound_differ.py` is <= 800 LOC (verify: `wc -l src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_differ.py`)\n- [ ] `inbound_differ.py` is absent from BOTH `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt` and `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt`, and its `docs/architecture.md` remedy row is deleted (verify: `! grep inbound_differ .github/module-size-allowlist.txt .github/module-size-ceilings.txt`)\n- [ ] `tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py` passes (verify: `pytest tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py -q`)\n- [ ] The reconciler test suite is green with no behavior change (verify: `pytest tests/unit/rebar_reconciler -q`)\n- [ ] Backward compatibility preserved: `inbound_differ._map_jira_to_local_fields`, `inbound_differ._JIRA_TO_LOCAL_STATUS`, `inbound_differ._assignee_matches`, `inbound_differ._normalize_jira_body` still resolve as module attributes (re-exported)\n\n## Notes\nLanded as its own Gerrit change (LLM-Review +1 AND Verified +1) before the ticket is closed. Refactor is mechanical/behavior-preserving, so E5 testing-plan is not-applicable (existing reconciler tests are the oracle).","id":"a130-2b7c-429c-43d1","parent_id":"716f-b917-9fc8-41f5","priority":1,"tags":["module-size"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Split inbound_differ.py: extract Jira->local translation into inbound_fields.py"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784392745104737001,"uuid":"91cf71a3-acc5-4e49-a59f-c2a916bd9ec1"}